HEADWORD: Sternforemost
<hw>Stern`fore"most`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>With the
stern, instead of the bow, in advance; hence, figuratively, in an
awkward, blundering manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A fatal genius for going <qex>sternforemost</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sternite</ent>⟦br⟧
